Arsenal travel to Sheffield United in the Premier League on Monday night. Unai Emery’s men are seeking to climb back into third place behind Manchester City, with a win at Bramall Lane. Sheffield will, however, have history on their side, as the Gunners have failed to win in the Steel City in eight league fixtures. Kick-off is 8pm West African time. Sheffield United XI vs Arsenal: Henderson, Basham, Egan, O’Connell, Stevens, Baldock, Norwood, Lundstram, Fleck, Mousset, McGoldrick Arsenal XI vs Sheffield United: Leno, Chambers, Sokratis, Luiz, Kolasinac, Xhaka, Guendouzi, Willock, Pepe, Saka, Aubameyang Monday, October 21
